Formal method (Based on WPI RBE 595) §
tag:#formalmethod
1. Formal specification §
1.1. Propositional logic §


Proposition: true or false


Atomic proposition (AP): the true or false does not depend on any other proposition
e.g.: 现在路口是绿灯


Logic connectives:


”: ‘AND’, : ‘OR’. : Negation


: Implication


  Example
运算顺序为从左至右，即
A: If it is a bear. 它是熊
B: then it can swim. 它会游泳
1. If A is false (it is not a bear), it might be able to swim (a fish) or not (a bird). 如果不是熊的话（A为false），可能会游泳也可能不会（比如是鱼或者是鸟），所以不是熊可以推出两种情况皆有可能（B既可能是true也可能是false）。
It can swim -&gt; B=T
It cannot swim -&gt; B=F
A false statement implies anything
2. If A is true (which it is a bear), it can swim (B=T). 如果是熊，一定会游泳



A and B does not necessary to have causal relationship (example)


: Equivalence 




















































0010011011011010001001101111


